Package com.example.chicksevent

Class TEST16_US020202_EntrantLocationMapUITest

java.lang.Object
com.example.chicksevent.TEST16_US020202_EntrantLocationMapUITest
public class TEST16_US020202_EntrantLocationMapUITest extends Object
UI tests for US 02.02.02: As an organizer I want to see on a map where entrants joined my event waiting list from.

These instrumented tests verify that the entrant location map is properly displayed and functional, allowing organizers to view where entrants joined the waiting list on an interactive map.

Note: For reliable test execution, it's recommended to disable animations on the test device/emulator before running these tests: 
 adb shell settings put global animator_duration_scale 0
 adb shell settings put global window_animation_scale 0
 adb shell settings put global transition_animation_scale 0
To re-enable animations after testing: 
 adb shell settings put global animator_duration_scale 1
 adb shell settings put global window_animation_scale 1
 adb shell settings put global transition_animation_scale 1

      public void organizer_mapView_displayedWhenViewingEntrantLocations()
      Test Case 1: Map view is displayed when organizer navigates to entrant locations. As an organizer, when I navigate to view entrant locations, I should see the map view displayed on the screen. Note: This test assumes navigation to EntrantLocationMapFragment is possible. In a real scenario, you would need to have an event with entrants.
